==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Runlet
<hw>Run"let</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Run</ets> +
<ets>-let</ets>.]</ety> <def>A little run or stream; a streamlet; a
brook.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>To trace out to its marshy source every <qex>runlet</qex> that has
cast in its tiny pitcherful with the rest.</q>
<rj><qau>Lowell.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Runlet</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Runlet
<hw>Run"let</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>Same as <er>Rundlet</er>.</def>
⟦ldquo⟧A stoup of sack, or a <xex>runlet</xex> of canary.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Sir W. Scott.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

